Advanced Guide
1
Open your browser and navigate to: "https://IP_Data_Collector/". You can also use
the a4conf icon on the Data Collector desktop.
2
Click "Advanced" within the main menu.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 2
3
Within the "Configuration" section, there is a JSON interface with all the
configurations of a4CONF. Click the "▶" icon to expand the desired section.
4
Click the "Active Dangerous Mode" button to manually edit the configurations.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 3
5
You can edit anything in this mode, keys and values.
6
Above the configuration tab, there are a number of tools to help you with the edit.
Click on the highlighted button to undo the last change (Control+Z).
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 4
7
Click the "Save" button to save the changes made.
8
Click the "Active Safe Mode" button to return to the Safe mode.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 5
9
Click the "Apply" button to apply the new configurations.
10
Move to "Terafence".
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 6
11
Select "Start" to start the corresponding service.
12
Select "Stop" to stop the corresponding service.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 7
Be careful to stop these services since they are the ones that enable the basic
operation of the device
13
Select "Restart" to restart the corresponding service.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 8
14
Move to "Recovery IP".
15
Click "Add recovery IP" to add a recovery IP to the Data Collector. By default this IP
address is already present, but there may be special cases where it has been
removed and with this button allows you to add it back. Adding a recovery IP can
be useful if you have forgotten the Data Collector IP address. Your PC must have
an IP on the same network as the recovery IP and a LAN cable must be connected
from the Data Collector to your PC.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 9
If the recovery IP address has been removed, as may be necessary if two a4GATEs
are connected to the same machine network, make sure that there is no IP
address conflict. in fact, in the case just described, if you restore the recovery IP on
more than one a4gate you will have an IP address conflict.
16
Click the "Remove recovery IP" button to remove the recover IP.
If you delete the recovery ip address, the Data Collector will only have the IP that
was assigned to it in the "Data collector -> Network -> Connection Parameters"
section. If you should forget the IP address and have not backed up the
configuration, you would have to perform several operations to retrieve the set IP
address.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 10
17
Move to "More".
18
Click the "Reboot Data Collector" button to reboot Data Collector. It will be
restarted 30 seconds after the button is pressed.
